qqiHLqLx","target":"reczuS92gSUORr83E","label":"participant"},{"source":"rechX4p94qqiHLqLx","target":"recZXzlSvnyNLqQxQ","label":"participant"},{"source":"rechX4p94qqiHLqLx","target":"recYlTJouLztJii9o","label":"location"},{"source":"rechX4p94qqiHLqLx","target":"rec7pLeyxV0yEdrcl","label":"predecessor"},{"source":"rechX4p94qqiHLqLx","target":"recmXmhZt51doQu7o","label":"part of"}],"verses":[{"id":"reczrUp2urLagFFDz","ref":"John.19.18","text":"Where they crucified him, and two other with him, on either side one, and Jesus in the midst.","year":33},{"id":"recTHhigB3OUXJZtA","ref":"John.19.19","text":"And Pilate wrote a title, and put it on the cross. And the writing was, JESUS OF NAZARETH THE KING OF THE JEWS.","year":33},{"id":"recwjPivjyqyvTuZF","ref":"John.19.20","text":"This title then read many of the Jews: for the place where Jesus was crucified was nigh to the city: and it was written in Hebrew, and Greek, and Latin.","year":33},{"id":"recdlUIfllqm3fLHy","ref":"John.19.21","text":"Then said the chief priests of the Jews to Pilate, Write not, The King of the Jews; but that he said, I am King of the Jews.","year":33},{"id":"rechBs1QyUICnAfzg","ref":"John.19.22","text":"Pilate answered, What I have written I have written.","year":33},{"id":"reccToMQwGWTMVcUi","ref":"John.19.23","text":"Then the soldiers, when they had crucified Jesus, took his garments, and made four parts, to every soldier a part; and also his coat: now the coat was without seam, woven from the top throughout.","year":33},{"id":"recAmhLRdqr8sqjUr","ref":"John.19.24","text":"They said therefore among themselves, Let us not rend it, but cast lots for it, whose it shall be: that the scripture might be fulfilled, which saith, They parted my raiment among them, and for my vesture they did cast lots. These things therefore the soldiers did.","year":33},{"id":"recxUTupNoAcuSsGe","ref":"John.19.25","text":"Now there stood by the cross of Jesus his mother, and his mother’s sister, Mary the wife of Cleophas, and Mary Magdalene.","year":33}]}
